<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-12-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-12-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="17" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d17">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Adams</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 832.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">London,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-12-16"><hi rend="italic">
                                        December</hi> 16, 1864</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: * * * * * * *</p>
                        <p>In accordance with the desire expressed in 1164, of the 29th of November,
                            I have transmitted to Lord Russell the information contained in General
                            Dix’s letter respecting the rebel organization at Marysburg, Prince
                            Edward’s county, in Canada.</p>
                        <p>It is announced that Parliament will meet for the despatch of business on
                            the 7th of February next.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>CHARLES FRANCIS ADAMS.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p> Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, &amp;c., &amp;c.,
                                &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>